# Calling `:` while STATE != 0 must throw -29 (compiler nesting)
# instead of silently re-entering compile mode and corrupting
# the dictionary.  Exercise via a compiled-body word that
# fakes compile state, executes colon under CATCH, and
# restores STATE — wrapping in a colon-def keeps the interpret
# loop running in interpret state throughout.
# requires: ' catch state
: provoke-nest   ( -- throw-code )
    state @ >r
    1 state !
    ['] : catch
    r> state !
;
provoke-nest . cr
bye
